- Come on.

108
00:08:38,746 --> 00:08:41,554
- Yukata, I'll bring you the giant poop.
- Come on, let's go.

109
00:08:41,578 --> 00:08:43,189
I'm looking forward to it.

110
00:08:43,799 --> 00:08:46,825
Giant poop.

111
00:08:54,644 --> 00:08:55,869
Amazing.

112
00:08:55,893 --> 00:08:57,470
That's a lot of drawings.

113
00:08:57,618 --> 00:08:58,594
Yeah.

114
00:08:58,860 --> 00:09:00,740
Since Christmas,
he's been drawing a lot.

115
00:09:01,070 --> 00:09:02,742
He said he's also
going to draw 100 friends.

116
00:09:02,766 --> 00:09:04,210
Is that so?

117
00:09:05,979 --> 00:09:07,981
Oh, I think that's you.

118
00:09:08,249 --> 00:09:09,416
Eh? Really?

119
00:09:09,440 --> 00:09:10,283
Yeah.

120
00:09:10,931 --> 00:09:12,842
But it's a mini Yutaka.

121
00:09:13,447 --> 00:09:14,387
It looks kinda like you.

122
00:09:15,734 --> 00:09:19,592
He made me so small, but still
managed to make me wear glasses.

123
00:09:19,617 --> 00:09:20,531
Whoa.

124
00:09:26,521 --> 00:09:27,634
Hello.

125
00:09:29,157 --> 00:09:30,345
Oh.

126
00:09:31,435 --> 00:09:32,569
Hello.

127
00:09:44,299 --> 00:09:45,200
Well...

128
00:09:47,303 --> 00:09:48,054
What?

129
00:09:51,092 --> 00:09:52,158
I...

130
00:09:54,747 --> 00:09:56,396
How should I say this?

131
00:09:59,532 --> 00:10:01,067
Well...

132
00:10:06,106 --> 00:10:07,107
Today,

133
00:10:08,442 --> 00:10:10,777
can I tell you my story?

134
00:10:24,791 --> 00:10:25,625
Yes.

135
00:10:28,564 --> 00:10:29,498
Go ahead.

136
00:10:37,137 --> 00:10:38,338
I...

137
00:10:44,326 --> 00:10:46,628
When I was a kid,

138
00:10:48,485 --> 00:10:50,750
my biological parents passed away.

139
00:10:53,879 --> 00:10:55,447
When I turned eight,

140
00:10:56,010 --> 00:11:00,627
a relative adopted me into their family.

141
00:11:03,190 --> 00:11:05,598
The family was very rich.

142
00:11:07,754 --> 00:11:10,637
My new dad and mom

143
00:11:12,148 --> 00:11:14,917
took good care of me,

144
00:11:15,221 --> 00:11:17,677
as if I were their real child.

145
00:11:20,696 --> 00:11:23,932
I think I was lucky.

146
00:11:26,873 --> 00:11:28,008
But...

147
00:11:28,336 --> 00:11:33,893
It seems the brother who's 5 years older
than me has never been able to accept me.

148
00:11:37,269 --> 00:11:38,270
You...

149
00:11:39,696 --> 00:11:41,264
don't even know how to eat, do you?

150
00:11:42,953 --> 00:11:43,903
Yuki.

151
00:11:45,676 --> 00:11:47,907
When he's around,
the food suddenly tastes bad.

152
00:11:49,313 --> 00:11:50,944
But, in hindsight,

153
00:11:51,077 --> 00:11:53,980
maybe it's just something
you'd consider "nothing."

154
00:11:54,004 --> 00:11:55,548
You did a good job.

155
00:11:58,482 --> 00:11:59,519
But...

156
00:12:01,695 --> 00:12:05,652
I felt pressured
by the atmosphere every day.

157
00:12:10,883 --> 00:12:12,298
Actually,

158
00:12:12,978 --> 00:12:14,634
this place is not even your real home.

159
00:12:15,657 --> 00:12:16,736
Dad,

160
00:12:17,135 --> 00:12:18,171
Mom,

161
00:12:18,726 --> 00:12:19,906
and everything.

162
00:12:20,616 --> 00:12:22,000
They all used to be mine.

163
00:12:23,654 --> 00:12:25,645
I don't know when it began,

164
00:12:27,171 --> 00:12:30,116
but I started eating alone.

165
00:12:31,751 --> 00:12:35,021
The tastes of the food I ate
every day back then.

166
00:12:36,558 --> 00:12:37,826
I...

167
00:12:38,208 --> 00:12:40,260
can barely remember them.

168
00:12:47,396 --> 00:12:49,068
After I grew up,

169
00:12:53,032 --> 00:12:54,607
even though I've moved out
of their home,

170
00:12:57,076 --> 00:12:58,444
and even though I have friends,

171
00:12:58,827 --> 00:13:00,580
and people I'm interested in,

172
00:13:07,063 --> 00:13:08,298
I'm still...

173
00:13:09,508 --> 00:13:13,263
scared of eating with people
at the same table.

174
00:13:17,869 --> 00:13:19,816
I can't remember

175
00:13:21,088 --> 00:13:23,002
my real parents' "flavor."

176
00:13:26,186 --> 00:13:27,554
I don't have...

177
00:13:30,710 --> 00:13:32,712
any good memories

178
00:13:33,118 --> 00:13:34,747
related to the dining table.

179
00:13:38,084 --> 00:13:39,786
When I think about that,

180
00:13:42,413 --> 00:13:44,415
I feel like, as a human,

181
00:13:45,127 --> 00:13:46,926
it's as if something is missing.

182
00:13:54,785 --> 00:13:55,768
But...

183
00:13:58,869 --> 00:14:00,337
At that moment...

184
00:14:02,275 --> 00:14:04,577
Yukata, you should eat with us.

185
00:14:04,741 --> 00:14:05,802
Yukata,

186
00:14:06,278 --> 00:14:07,847
having you here is enough.

187
00:14:09,196 --> 00:14:10,850
Meeting you two

188
00:14:16,089 --> 00:14:17,256
and...

189
00:14:17,966 --> 00:14:19,258
eating...

190
00:14:19,879 --> 00:14:21,461
together,

191
00:14:24,398 --> 00:14:25,698
I feel...

192
00:14:26,436 --> 00:14:29,602
happy for the first time
since I was born.

193
00:14:33,331 --> 00:14:34,340
So...

194
00:14:39,173 --> 00:14:40,446
I mean...

195
00:14:41,614 --> 00:14:44,484
What I want to tell you is...

196
00:14:55,574 --> 00:14:56,808
Thank you.

197
00:14:59,549 --> 00:15:02,502
For coming up
and talking to me back then.

198
00:15:17,306 --> 00:15:18,418
Yutaka.

199
00:15:27,702 --> 00:15:28,528
Here.

200
00:15:28,567 --> 00:15:30,378
Ah, thank you.

201
00:15:32,865 --> 00:15:38,037
Yukata, I finished the poop.
Come look, quickly.

202
00:15:40,773 --> 00:15:45,578
Minoru, you made Yukata cry.

203
00:15:45,602 --> 00:15:49,482
Yukata, don't cry.

204
00:15:49,506 --> 00:15:52,819
- Yukata.
- What? Don't cry with him.

205
00:15:52,843 --> 00:15:55,388
- Yukata, don't cry.
- I'm sorry.

206
00:15:56,075 --> 00:15:58,124
- Yukata.
- Quit it.

207
00:15:58,378 --> 00:16:00,493
Tane, I got it.

208
00:16:00,517 --> 00:16:01,561
Quiet.

209
00:16:01,585 --> 00:16:03,029
Come on.

210
00:16:03,053 --> 00:16:04,030
Come on.

211
00:16:14,440 --> 00:16:15,975
Tane, are you okay now?

212
00:16:16,248 --> 00:16:17,176
Yeah.

213
00:16:18,711 --> 00:16:20,980
Sorry for alarming you.

214
00:16:22,181 --> 00:16:24,650
Yukata, were you bullied?

215
00:16:25,474 --> 00:16:26,285
Eh?

216
00:16:27,191 --> 00:16:28,125
No.

217
00:16:28,711 --> 00:16:30,590
Why did you cry?

218
00:16:33,259 --> 00:16:35,695
Did something sad happen?

219
00:16:41,400 --> 00:16:44,036
Do you want me to pat your head
to calm you down?

220
00:16:49,375 --> 00:16:50,743
There,

221
00:16:50,907 --> 00:16:52,378
there.

222
00:16:52,566 --> 00:16:53,913
There,

223
00:16:54,265 --> 00:16:55,648
there.

224
00:16:55,982 --> 00:16:57,316
There...

225
00:17:07,693 --> 00:17:09,295
Tane, thank you.

226
00:17:16,369 --> 00:17:18,037
I'm okay now.

227
00:17:23,961 --> 00:17:26,345
Is there a hungry kid here?

228
00:17:26,533 --> 00:17:28,481
Want a rice ball?

229
00:17:28,505 --> 00:17:30,283
He's here. Rice Ball Man.

230
00:17:30,307 --> 00:17:31,984
He has a face too.

231
00:17:33,653 --> 00:17:36,956
Tane asked for it,
so I made Rice Ball Man the Series.

232
00:17:36,981 --> 00:17:38,457
- Eh?
- It's yummy.

233
00:17:40,265 --> 00:17:41,566
Which one do you want, Tane?

234
00:17:42,216 --> 00:17:44,136
This one. Cheese Rice Ball Man.

235
00:17:44,169 --> 00:17:45,298
- This one?
- Yes.

236
00:17:45,771 --> 00:17:46,771
What about you, Yutaka?

237
00:17:47,433 --> 00:17:49,302
Then, I'll take this one.

238
00:17:49,326 --> 00:17:50,202
Okay.

239
00:17:50,484 --> 00:17:51,604
All right.

240
00:17:51,628 --> 00:17:52,572
Wow.

241
00:17:52,689 --> 00:17:54,640
It's so cute that
I don't want to eat it.

242
00:17:58,221 --> 00:17:59,045
Mmm.

243
00:18:01,641 --> 00:18:02,982
No one cares.

244
00:18:03,006 --> 00:18:03,816
Yummy.

245
00:18:04,020 --> 00:18:05,318
Yummy.

246
00:18:33,085 --> 00:18:35,715
This reminds me of the first day we met.

247
00:18:36,025 --> 00:18:36,849
Hmm?

248
00:18:38,597 --> 00:18:42,254
In the park,
Tane kept staring at my rice ball.

249
00:18:43,289 --> 00:18:44,323
Grenade.

250
00:18:44,683 --> 00:18:46,292
Yeah, grenade.

251
00:18:46,557 --> 00:18:48,694
Minoru totally lost it back then.

252
00:18:50,453 --> 00:18:53,165
Hey, let's make
our Rice Ball Mans fight.

253
00:18:53,415 --> 00:18:54,533
How?

254
00:18:54,557 --> 00:18:57,803
First, do this
to charge up the rice ball.

255
00:18:57,827 --> 00:18:58,471
Okay.

256
00:18:58,495 --> 00:19:00,693
