287
00:20:36,043 --> 00:20:38,270
I just want to try it on.

288
00:20:38,403 --> 00:20:40,947
I see. It's normal
for people with good eyesight.

289
00:20:44,293 --> 00:20:46,145
What you do think? Does it suit me?

290
00:20:48,214 --> 00:20:49,348
It does.

291
00:20:49,393 --> 00:20:50,349
That's great.

292
00:20:59,671 --> 00:21:01,794
Thank you. I'm always thankful to you.

293
00:21:02,428 --> 00:21:03,229
Hmm?

294
00:21:09,201 --> 00:21:11,303
I'm glad you're here with me.

295
00:21:20,913 --> 00:21:21,947
Minoru.

296
00:21:23,849 --> 00:21:24,917
What's wrong?

297
00:21:26,677 --> 00:21:27,620
Nothing.

298
00:21:28,972 --> 00:21:30,055
Well...

299
00:21:34,655 --> 00:21:35,957
I mean...

300
00:21:36,690 --> 00:21:40,366
I'm the one who should thank you.

301
00:21:50,487 --> 00:21:52,344
You may not remember,

302
00:21:53,508 --> 00:21:54,576
but back then,

303
00:21:55,286 --> 00:21:57,583
you were the one who talked to me first.

304
00:22:00,441 --> 00:22:01,320
Eh?

305
00:22:07,648 --> 00:22:08,727
Minoru.

306
00:23:09,901 --> 00:23:10,701
(Next episode)

307
00:23:10,714 --> 00:23:12,358
Was it a dream?

308
00:23:12,382 --> 00:23:15,027
(That meeting came back to memory)
Actually, before I felt sad,

309
00:23:15,027 --> 00:23:16,795
(That meeting came back to memory)
I felt a little relieved.

310
00:23:17,312 --> 00:23:18,931
(Going in different directions)
How long...

311
00:23:19,056 --> 00:23:21,484
(Two people being awkward)
have I been alone on weekends?

312
00:23:22,391 --> 00:23:24,503
The feeling still lingers.
